Sentencas: An oxygen ion conductor, Y0.25Bi0.75O1.5 (YSB), infiltrated La0.6Sr0.4CO0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) is prepared as the electrode of proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells (H SOFCs).
Titulo: Highly active YSB infiltrated LSCF cathode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The YSB is deposited onto LSCF surface by infiltration way at 600 degrees C with a good chemical compatibility.
Titulo: Highly active YSB infiltrated LSCF cathode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of YSB infiltrated LSCF electrode is evaluated regarding the infiltration process.
Titulo: Highly active YSB infiltrated LSCF cathode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: When the loading of YSB increases, the interfacial polarization resistance (R-P) of the symmetric cell decreases gradually and then increases.
Titulo: Highly active YSB infiltrated LSCF cathode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results of symmetric cell and single cell test indicate that the electrochemical activity of YSB infiltrated LSCF cathode is higher than that using traditional mixed SSC-SDC cathode.
Titulo: Highly active YSB infiltrated LSCF cathode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The encouraging results open a promising strategy to develop cathode materials for H-SOFCs at low temperature.
Titulo: Highly active YSB infiltrated LSCF cathode for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells
